      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(sessions): add adaptive reset mode with daily AND idle semantics",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: Session reset currently supports only `daily` and `idle`, and when both are configured the behavior is OR-based, which can reset an active conversation as soon as the daily boundary passes.\n- Why it matters: Some users want the daily rollover guard without interrupting active conversations, meaning reset should happen only after the boundary has passed and the session has gone idle.\n- What changed: Added `mode: \"adaptive\"` as a narrow reset mode that requires both the daily boundary and the idle window before a session becomes stale, and updated the schema/help/session wiring to match.\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary): This PR does not add new reset fields, change the default reset mode, or alter existing `daily` and `idle` semantics.\n\n## Change Type (select all)\n\n- [ ] Bug fix\n- [x] Feature\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\n- [ ] Docs\n- [ ] Security hardening\n- [ ] Chore/infra\n\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\n- [ ] Memory / storage\n- [ ] Integrations\n- [x] API / contracts\n- [x] UI / DX\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n\n- Closes #43738\n- Related #44489\n- [ ] This PR fixes a bug or regression\n\n## Root Cause (if applicable)\n\n- Root cause: N/A\n- Missing detection / guardrail: N/A\n- Contributing context (if known): N/A\n\n## Regression Test Plan (if applicable)\n\nN/A\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\n- `session.reset.mode` accepts a new value: `\"adaptive\"`.\n- `adaptive` resets a session only when both conditions are met:\n  - the daily reset boundary has passed\n  - the configured idle window has expired\n- Existing `daily` and `idle` behavior remains unchanged.\n\n## Diagram (if applicable)\n\n```text\nBefore:\n[daily stale] OR [idle stale] -> reset\n\nAfter:\nmode=daily/idle -> existing behavior unchanged\nmode=adaptive -> [daily stale] AND [idle stale] -> reset\n```\n\n## Security Impact (required)\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? (`No`)\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? (`No`)\n- New/changed network calls? (`No`)\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? (`No`)\n- Data access scope changed? (`No`)\n- If any `Yes`, explain risk + mitigation:\n\n## Repro + Verification\n\n### Environment\n\n- OS: macOS\n- Runtime/container: local source checkout\n- Model/provider: N/A\n- Integration/channel (if any): N/A\n- Relevant config (redacted): session reset policy with `atHour` and `idleMinutes`\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Configure session reset mode as `adaptive` with `atHour` and `idleMinutes`.\n2. Evaluate freshness when only the daily boundary is crossed.\n3. Evaluate freshness when only the idle window expires.\n4. Evaluate freshness when both are true.\n\n### Expected\n\n- Daily-only stale: session remains fresh.\n- Idle-only stale: session remains fresh.\n- Both stale: session resets.\n- Existing `daily` and `idle` modes behave exactly as before.\n\n### Actual\n\n- Added adaptive-mode policy tests plus schema/session behavior coverage.\n- Updated schema/help/generated config surfaces and session handling.\n- Focused Vitest suite passed.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `session.reset.mode: \"adaptive\"` should keep an existing session fresh when only the daily boundary or only the idle window is stale, and should roll the session only when both conditions are stale.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS, running this branch's real `initSessionState` path against a temporary on-disk session store under `~/.openclaw/state/tmp`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a one-shot runtime script from the branch with `pnpm exec tsx` that seeded three real session rows, configured `session.reset.mode: \"adaptive\"`, and called `initSessionState` for daily-only, idle-only, and both-stale cases.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from that real runtime path:\n\n  ```text\n  OpenClaw adaptive reset runtime proof\n  tempStore=/Users/mantis/.openclaw/state/tmp/openclaw-adaptive-real-proof-hn8QYH/sessions.json\n  policy=mode:adaptive atHour:8 idleMinutes:60\n  daily-only stale stays fresh: isNewSession=false previous=adaptive-daily-only result=adaptive-daily-only\n  idle-only stale stays fresh: isNewSession=false previous=adaptive-idle-only result=adaptive-idle-only\n  daily+idle stale rolls session: isNewSession=true previous=adaptive-both-stale result=45327a3a-ef16-44a5-a950-96a8bc242f29\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The actual session runtime preserved the current session when only one adaptive condition was stale, and created a new session only when both daily and idle conditions were stale.\n- **What was not tested:** Full interactive Telegram delivery flow; this proof targets the real OpenClaw session initialization/reset path that owns the adaptive rollover decision.\n\n## Evidence\n\nAttach at least one:\n\n- [x] Failing test/log before + passing after\n- [ ] Trace/log snippets\n- [ ] Screenshot/recording\n- [ ] Perf numbers (if relevant)\n\n## Human Verification (required)\n\nWhat you personally verified (not just CI), and how:\n\n- Verified scenarios:\n  - adaptive policy stays fresh when only one side is stale\n  - adaptive policy resets when both daily and idle conditions are stale\n  - schema accepts `mode: \"adaptive\"`\n  - session-related tests still pass with the new mode wired through\n- Edge cases checked:\n  - adaptive mode defaults an idle window when omitted in policy resolution\n  - schema/help/generated config surfaces remain aligned\n- What you did **not** verify:\n  - remote GitHub CI beyond the local focused suite and `check:changed`\n\n## Review Conversations\n\n- [x] I replied to or resolved every bot review conversation I addressed in this PR.\n- [x] I left unresolved only the conversations that still need reviewer or maintainer judgment.\n\nIf a bot review conversation is addressed by this PR, resolve that conversation yourself. Do not leave bot review conversation cleanup for maintainers.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? (`Yes`)\n- Config/env changes? (`No`)\n- Migration needed? (`No`)\n- If yes, exact upgrade steps:\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- Risk: AND/OR freshness logic could be implemented incorrectly and silently change reset behavior.\n  - Mitigation: Added focused policy tests for both-one-neither stale combinations while preserving existing mode behavior.\n- Risk: Config/schema layers could drift if `adaptive` is added in one validation surface but not another.\n  - Mitigation: update type union, Zod schema, generated schema/help text, and session wiring together.\n- Risk: stale-session reason/reporting paths could become misleading if adaptive mode is only partially wired.\n  - Mitigation: included session-related tests and the current session/reset handling surfaces in the same change.\n\n## Latest local validation\n\nCurrent head: `b61b8af26c1e2903afec2810937d2ac3dc24c78e`\n\nBranch history: rebuilt from current upstream into one feature commit and force-pushed after dropping stale rebase/sync churn.\n\nLocal validation on the squashed head:\n\n- `pnpm config:docs:check` — passed\n- `pnpm test src/config/sessions/sessions.test.ts src/config/zod-schema.session-maintenance-extensions.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session-hooks-context.test.ts` — passed\n- `pnpm deadcode:unused-files` — passed\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8` — passed\n\nGitHub checks on the current head while updating this proof:\n\n- `gh pr checks 71400 --repo openclaw/openclaw --json name,state,workflow` — 124 success, 28 skipped, 1 neutral, 0 failing, 0 pending\n- `gh pr view 71400 --repo openclaw/openclaw --json mergeable,headRefOid` — head matches `b61b8af26c1e2903afec2810937d2ac3dc24c78e`; mergeability currently reports `MERGEABLE`\n",
